docs.abstract: The growing rift between Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren rose to the surface in the Democratic debate, and the candidates also sparred over their stances on war.
docs.snippet: The growing rift between Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren rose to the surface in the Democratic debate, and the candidates also sparred over their stances on war.
docs.lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The Democratic presidential candidates clashed in starkly personal terms Tuesday over who had the best chance to defeat President Trump, as Senator Elizabeth Warren sought to jump-start her campaign in the last debate before the Iowa caucuses by highlighting her electoral success and that of other female candidates in the Trump era.

headline.main: Gender, War and Taking On Trump: Democrats Spar Just Weeks Before Voting
headline.print_headline: Gender and War Dominate Debate by 6 Democrats

docs.abstract: Bernie Sanders has raised more money from Latino donors than any of his Democratic rivals and he leads the field with Latino support in a new poll.
docs.snippet: Bernie Sanders has raised more money from Latino donors than any of his Democratic rivals and he leads the field with Latino support in a new poll.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Three months before anyone starts voting in the Democratic primaries, advisers for Bernie Sanders are confident about the new voters they are registering in Iowa. They expect a decisive victory in New Hampshire, where Mr. Sanders, the senator from neighboring Vermont, is seen as a local. And in California, a state the campaign views as clearing a path to the nomination, they believe Mr. Sanders has a clear advantage with the not-so-secret weapon of Latino voters.

headline.main: ‘Tío Bernie’ Is Courting the Latino Votes He Needs to Win
headline.print_headline: Sanders, or ‘Tío Bernie,’ Cultivates Latino Democrats

docs.abstract: Here’s how the four senators running for president are handling a civic obligation they can’t postpone.

docs.lead_paragraph: Last January, Representative Rashida Tlaib of Michigan exploded onto the national political scene with her expletive-laden cry to impeach President Trump. A little more than a year later, senators arrived in their chamber today to somberly sign an oath to deliver “impartial justice” in Mr. Trump’s impeachment trial.

docs.lead_paragraph: MARSHALLTOWN, Iowa — A nearly yearlong run of good will between two of the leading progressives in the 2020 presidential race, Senator Elizabeth Warren and Senator Bernie Sanders, appears to be evaporating in the run-up to the Iowa caucuses.

docs.lead_paragraph: The American strike in Baghdad that killed the Iranian general Qassim Suleimani thrust foreign policy to the center of the Democratic presidential race, drawing expressions of grave concern from the leading candidates and stoking a new debate in the party about the American military presence in the Middle East.
